## Summary
2-4 concise sentences tailored to the target role. No first person. No emotional language. Use job-description keywords naturally.
State the candidate’s target-relevant identity, years of relevant experience when supported, strongest domain or platform alignment, core technical or functional stack, and 2-3 differentiators proven in the experience section.
Include one concrete proof point if it fits naturally. Do not force a metric into the summary.
Include a Summary when it strengthens positioning, especially for senior candidates, specialized roles, or career pivots. Omit it if it would only repeat the experience section without adding focus.

## Skills
Hard skills only. 4-6 categories, one line each. Use job-description terminology where appropriate and supported by candidate data.
No soft skills, no values, no "team player," no "strong communicator."
Use grouped categories with comma-separated items. No tables.
Put the most relevant skills first and include only skills the candidate can defend in an interview.

## Experience
Role Title | Company | Month YYYY - Month YYYY | Location
