- Within each role, prioritize the bullets that best match the target job, even if those bullets represent only one part of the broader role.
- The most recent and/or most relevant role should usually have the most detail. Reduce detail as roles become older or less relevant unless an older role adds critical evidence for the target job.
- When supported, frame bullets to show change, such as before/after state, manual-to-automated workflow, baseline-to-improved metric, or problem-to-solution-to-impact.
